A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing April 5, 2025, as Run Atlanta 5K Day; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the 100 Black Men of Atlanta Inc., under the leadership of Chairman Sid
3 Barron, proudly presents the Run Atlanta 5K, an event that symbolizes a collective
4 commitment to health, wellness, and the reduction of violence in our communities; and
5 WHEREAS, this event will unite individuals across the City of Atlanta and the State of
6 Georgia in promoting physical well-being, peace, and safety; and
7 WHEREAS, the Health and Wellness Committee of the 100 Black Men of Atlanta, led by
8 Dr. Winston Carhee, will focus on promoting the importance of fitness, healthy living, and
9 disease prevention through the 5K race and related activities, and the Violence Prevention
10 Committee, led by Joshua Byrd, will host the Sunrise Prayer for Violence Prevention and the
11 Walk for Peace & Well-being, all of which reflects a collective resolve to combat gun
12 violence and work toward a peaceful future for our youth, families, and neighborhoods; and
13 WHEREAS, this event serves as a powerful reminder of the ongoing need to address the
14 impact of violence on our communities, particularly as we honor the life of Kenneth Collier
15 Jr., a 17-year-old advocate for peace who tragically lost his life to gun violence and whose
