16 story, alongside that of his mother, Tamika Trimble, who was also a victim of gun violence,
17 underscores the urgency of our shared mission to prevent future tragedies like theirs; and
18 WHEREAS, the 100 Black Men of Atlanta stands alongside local leaders, organizations, and
19 judicial officials in Fulton County and across Georgia, working together to end violence and
20 create safer environments for all residents, and their unwavering commitment to justice,
21 peace, and community empowerment makes it possible for us to envision and work toward
22 a brighter, more peaceful future; and
23 WHEREAS, the Run Atlanta 5K event offers an opportunity for us all to come together in
24 solidarity while promoting the values of health, wellness, and violence prevention that are
25 crucial to building strong, thriving communities, and we celebrate this initiative and
26 encourage all citizens to participate, support the cause, and continue working toward a future
27 free from violence.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body recognize April 5, 2025, as Run Atlanta 5K Day.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 public and the press.
